<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="../../w/index-title=Imagine_(song)&action=edit&section=8.php.html" title="Edit section: Notes">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Notes">Notes</span></h2>
<div class="reflist references-column-width" style="-moz-column-width: 30em; -webkit-column-width: 30em; column-width: 30em; list-style-type: decimal;">
<ol class="references">
<li id="cite_note-8"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-8">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">The lyrical content of "Imagine" relates to Lennon's concept of <a href="Nutopia" title="Nutopia">Nutopia: The Country of Peace</a>, which he invented in 1973. Lennon included a symbolically mute anthem to this country on his album <i><a href="Mind_Games" title="Mind Games">Mind Games</a></i> released later that year.<sup id="cite_ref-FOOTNOTEBlaney200782_7-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-FOOTNOTEBlaney200782-7"><span>[</span>7<span>]</span></a></sup></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-39"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-39">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">In 1991, the BBC restricted "Imagine" from airplay during the <a href="Gulf_War" title="Gulf War">Gulf War</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-peddle_38-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-peddle-38"><span>[</span>37<span>]</span></a></sup></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-45"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-45">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Yoko Ono dedicated the <a href="Imagine_Peace_Tower" title="Imagine Peace Tower">Imagine Peace Tower</a> in <a href="Iceland" title="Iceland">Iceland</a>, in 2007.<sup id="cite_ref-44" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-44"><span>[</span>42<span>]</span></a></sup></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-58"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-58">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a href="Peter_Gabriel" title="Peter Gabriel">Peter Gabriel</a> performed the song during the <a href="2006_Winter_Olympics" title="2006 Winter Olympics">2006 Winter Olympics</a> opening ceremony.<sup id="cite_ref-57" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-57"><span>[</span>54<span>]</span></a></sup></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-62"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-62">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a href="Madonna_(entertainer)" title="Madonna (entertainer)">Madonna</a> included the song in her setlist during the 2004 <a href="Re-Invention_World_Tour" title="Re-Invention World Tour">Re-Invention World Tour</a>, and released it on the live album and DVD documentary <i><a href="I'm_Going_to_Tell_You_a_Secret" title="I'm Going to Tell You a Secret">I'm Going to Tell You a Secret</a></i> in 2006.<sup id="cite_ref-61" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-61"><span>[</span>57<span>]</span></a></sup></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-66"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-66">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">The first adaptation of the original 8-track recording of "Imagine", Lennon also appeared in video.<sup id="cite_ref-HuffPo12_65-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-HuffPo12-65"><span>[</span>60<span>]</span></a></sup></span></li>
</ol>
</div>
